                <h3><ins>WHAT IS MENTAL HEALTH ?</ins></h3><br>
                <p>Mental health refers to a person's overall psychological well-being. 
                   It includes a person's emotional, social, and psychological state, and how they handle life's ups and downs. 
                   Mental health encompasses a range of factors, including thoughts, feelings, behaviors, and relationships with others.
                   Good mental health allows individuals to enjoy life, cope with stress, and contribute to their communities in positive ways. 
                   Mental health can be influenced by a variety of factors, including genetics, life experiences, and environmental factors. 
                   When someone experiences poor mental health, they may have difficulty managing emotions, relationships, and daily life tasks.
                </p><br>
                <br>
                <h3>IMPORTANCE OF MENTAL HEALTH</h3><br>
                <p>Mental health is an essential component of overall health and well-being.
                   Here are some reasons why mental health is important:</p><br>
                   <ul>
                     <li>
                        <p>Mental health is closely tied to emotional health. When we're struggling with mental health issues, we may experience a range of negative emotions, including anxiety, depression, and anger.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Mental health is also linked to productivity. When we're struggling with mental health issues, it can be challenging to stay focused and motivated at work or in other areas of our lives.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p>Mental health can have a significant impact on our relationships with others. When we're struggling with mental health issues, it can be difficult to maintain healthy relationships with our loved ones.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li>
                        <p> Mental health can have a significant impact on our daily lives. 
                            When we're struggling with mental health issues, it can affect our ability to function at work, in school, and in our personal relationships.</p>
                     </li>
                   </ul>
                   <br>
                   <br>
                <h3>THE MENTAL HEALTH PROBLEMS</h3><br>
                <p>Some common mental health problems include anxiety disorders, depression, bipolar disorder, schizophrenia, and eating disorders. These conditions can be very difficult to deal with, but they are treatable. 
                    Seeking professional help from a mental health provider can be an important first step in managing these conditions and improving overall mental health.
                </p>
